  "prompt": "What are the legal precedents related to money laundering cases?",
  "response": "There are several important legal precedents related to money laundering cases. Some key examples include:\n\n1. United States v. Levin (2010)\n- Established stricter definitions of financial reporting requirements\n- Clarified standards for prosecuting complex money laundering schemes\n\n2. Bank of Credit and Commerce International (BCCI) case (1991)\n- Major international case highlighting cross-border money laundering\n- Led to significant reforms in banking regulation\n\n3. Proceeds of Crime Act (UK, 2002)\n- Expanded legal frameworks for detecting and prosecuting money laundering\n- Created more comprehensive reporting requirements for financial institutions\n\nThese cases have helped shape modern anti-money laundering legal standards. However, specific details can vary by jurisdiction and context.\n\nWould you be interested in discussing specific legal nuances or hearing about more recent precedents?",
